Edison Chief Says EDF Will Replace Him, Panorama Economy Reports

-- B y   A l e s s a n d r a   M i g l i a c c i o
-- 
2011-03-30T13:43:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/edison-chief-says-edf-will-replace-him-panorama-economy-reports.html
Edison SpA (EDN)  Chief Executive Officer
Umberto Quadrino said French shareholder Electricite de France
SA plans to replace him, according to an interview he gave to
weekly magazine  Panorama Economy.   “The French chose to exercise a right that is theirs,” he
told the magazine. according to an e-mailed statement containing
a preview of the interview sent by Panorama Economy. “These
things happen, life is long.”  EDF, through an agreement among the owners of the holding
company that controls Edison, has the right to name the CEO
while Italian shareholders can name the company’s chairman. EDF
controls about 50 percent of Edison through direct and indirect
stakes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alessandra Migliaccio in Rome at 
 amigliaccio@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Will Kennedy  at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net . 